headline: Constellation Energy Texas Data Center Deal Tests Valuation And Concentration Risks
summary: Constellation Energy’s Calpine unit has secured a new power agreement with data center operator CyrusOne in Texas. The deal covers up to 760 megawatts of power capacity for CyrusOne’s planned Texas data centers. The agreement includes exclusive rights for potential further expansion tied to CyrusOne’s future facilities in the state. For Constellation Energy, ticker NasdaqGS:CEG, this new agreement arrives after a mixed run for the share price. The stock closed at $276.12, with an 11.8% gain...
